obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (27983)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content `This Act may be called the Delimitation Act, 2002.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510&sectionId=27983&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (27984)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. The words "but does not include the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 62 (w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510&sectionId=27984&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "article"`
  line `means an article of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(b) "associate member" means a member nominated under section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) "Commission" means the Delimitation Commission constituted under section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) "Election Commission" means the Election Commission referred to in article 324;`
  line
  line `(e) "member" means a member of the Commission and includes the Chairperson; and`
  line
  line `(f) “State” includes a Union territory having a Legislative Assembly ^1***`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (27985)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of Delimitation Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 2004, s. 2, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 31-10-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510&sectionId=27985&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `As soon as may be after the commencement of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government shall constitute a Commission to be called the Delimitation Commission`
  line `which shall consist of three members as follows:--`
  line
  line `(a) one member, who shall be a person who is or has been a Judge of the Supreme Court, to be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government who shall be the Chairperson of the Commission;`
  line
  line `(b) the Chief Election Commissioner or an Election Commissioner nominated by the Chief`
  line `Election Commissioner, ex officio:`
  line
  line `Provided that after the nomination of an Election Commissioner as a member under this clause,`
  line `no further nomination under this clause shall be made except to fill the casual vacancy of such`
  line `member under section 6; and`
  line
  line `(c) the State Election Commissioner of concerned State, ex officio.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation.-- For the purposes of clause (c), the State Election Commissioner of concerned`
  line State,--
  line
  line `(i) in respect of the duties of the Commission relating to a State (other than the States of`
  line `Meghalaya, Mizoram and Nagaland), means the State Election Commissioner appointed by the`
  line `Governor of that State under clause (1) of article 243K; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in respect of the duties of the Commission relating to the State of Meghalaya or the State of`
  line `Mizoram or the State of Nagaland, as the case may be, means a person nominated by the Governor of`
  line `that State for such purposes].`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (27986)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Duties of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 2004, s. 3, for "1991" (w.e.f. 31-10-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510&sectionId=27986&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The readjustment made, on the basis of the census figures as`
  line `ascertained at the census held in the year 1971 by the Delimitation Commission constituted under section`
  line `3 of the Delimitation Act, 1972 (76 of 1972), of the allocation of seats in the House of the People to the`
  line `several States and the total number of seats in the Legislative Assembly of each State shall be deemed to`
  line `be the readjustment made by the Commission for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1) and any other law for the time being in force, the`
  line `Commission shall readjust the division of each State into territorial constituencies for the purpose of elections to the House of the People and to the State Legislative Assembly on the basis of the census`
  line `figures as ascertained at the census held in the year ^1[2001]:`
  line
  line `Provided that where on such readjustment only one seat is allocated in the House of the People to a`
  line `State, the whole of that State shall form one territorial constituency for the purpose of elections to the`
  line `House of the People from that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (27987)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Associate members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510&sectionId=27987&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall associate with itself for the purpose of assisting it`
  line `in its duties in respect of each State, ten persons five of whom shall be members of the House of the`
  line `People representing that State and five shall be members of the Legislative Assembly of that State:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the number of members of the House of the People representing any State is five`
  line `or less, then, all such members shall be the associate members for that State and in the latter case the total`
  line `number of associate members shall be less than ten by such number as by which the total number of`
  line `members of the House of the People representing that State is less than five.`
  line
  line `(2) The persons to be so associated from each State shall be nominated, in the case of the members of`
  line `the House of the People, by the Speaker of that House, and in the case of members of a Legislative`
  line `Assembly, by the Speaker of that Assembly, having due regard to the composition of the House or, as the`
  line `case may be, of the Assembly.`
  line
  line `(3) The first nominations to be made under sub-section --(2)`
  line
  line `(a) shall be made by the Speakers of the several Legislative Assemblies within one month, and by`
  line `the Speaker of the House of the People within two months, of the commencement of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(b) shall be communicated to the Chief Election Commissioner, and where the nominations are`
  line `made by the Speaker of a Legislative Assembly, also to the Speaker of the House of the People.`
  line
  line `(4) None of the associate members shall have a right to vote or to sign any decision of the`
  line Commission.
  line
  line `(5) The Commission shall have power to call upon--`
  line
  line `(a) the Registrar-General and Census Commissioner, India or his nominee; or`
  line
  line `(b) the Surveyor General of India or his nominee; or`
  line
  line `(c) any other officer of the Central Government or State Government; or`
  line
  line `(d) any expert in geographical information system; or`
  line
  line `(e) any other person,`
  line
  line `whose expertise and knowledge are considered necessary by the Commission to provide assistance to it in`
  line `addition to the assistance provided by the persons referred to in sub-section (1) and the officers and`
  line `persons so called upon shall be duty bound to assist the Commission.`
  line
  line `(6) The Secretary to the Election Commission shall be the ex officio Secretary of the Commission and`
  line `shall discharge his functions with the assistance of the employees of the Election Commission under the`
  line `supervision of the Chairperson of the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (27988)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Casual vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510&sectionId=27988&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `If the office of the Chairperson or of a member or of an associate member`
  line `falls vacant owing to his death or resignation, it shall be filled as soon as may be practicable by the`
  line `Central Government or the Speaker concerned under and in accordance with the provisions of section 3`
  line `or, as the case may be, of section 5.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (27989)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Procedure and powers of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510&sectionId=27989&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall determine its own`
  line `procedure and shall, in the performance of its functions, have all the powers of a civil court under the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit, in respect of the following matters,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of witnesses;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the production of any document; and`
  line
  line `(c) requisitioning any public record from any court or office.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall have power to require any person to furnish any information on such points`
  line `or matters as in the opinion of the Commission may be useful for, or relevant to, any matter under the`
  line `consideration of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission may authorise any of its members to exercise any of the powers conferred on it`
  line `by clauses (a) to (c) of sub-section (1) and sub-section (2), and any order made or act done in exercise of`
  line `any of those powers by the member authorised by the Commission in that behalf shall be deemed to be`
  line `the order or act, as the case may be, of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) If there is a difference of opinion among the members, the opinion of the majority shall prevail,`
  line `and acts and orders of the Commission shall be expressed in terms of the views of the majority.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commission as well as any group of associate members shall have power to act`
  line `notwithstanding the temporary absence of a member or associate member or the existence of a vacancy in`
  line `the Commission or in that or any other group of associate members; and no act or proceeding of the`
  line `Commission or of any group of associate members shall be invalid or called in question on the ground`
  line `merely of such temporary absence or of the existence of such vacancy.`
  line
  line `(6) The Commission shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of sections 345 and 346 of`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of enforcing the attendance of witnesses, the local limits of the`
  line `jurisdiction of the Commission shall be the limits of the territory of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (27990)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Readjustment of number of seats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510&sectionId=27990&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall, having regard to the provisions of`
  line `articles 81, 170, 330 and 332, and also, in relation to the Union territories, except National Capital`
  line `Territory of Delhi, sections 3 and 39 of the Government of Union Territories Act, 1963 (20 of 1963) and`
  line `in relation to the National Capital Territory of Delhi sub-clause (b) of clause (2) of article 239AA, by`
  line `order, determine,--`
  line
  line `(a) on the basis of the census figures as ascertained at the census held in the year 1971 and`
  line `subject to the provisions of section 4, the number of seats in the House of the People to be allocated to`
  line `each State and determine on the basis of the census figures as ascertained at the ^*[census held in the`
  line `year ^1[2001]] the number of seats, if any, to be reserved for the Scheduled Castes and for the`
  line `Scheduled Tribes of the State; and`
  line
  line `(b) on the basis of the census figures as ascertained at the census held in the year 1971 and`
  line `subject to the provisions of section 4, the total number of seats to be assigned to the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of each State and determine on the basis of the census figures as ascertained at the ^*[census`
  line `held in the year ^1[2001]] the number of seats, if any, to be reserved for the Scheduled Castes and for`
  line `the Scheduled Tribes of the State:`
  line
  line `Provided that the total number of seats assigned to the Legislative Assembly of any State under clause`
  line
  line `(b) shall be an integral multiple of the number of seats in the House of the People allocated to that State`
  line `under clause (a).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `*. For the purposes of delimitation of Assembly and Parliamentary Constituencies, the words and figures "census held in the year 2001" wherever occurring, shall be construed as words and figures "census held in the year 2011" vide Act No. 34 of 2019, s. 62(1)(b) (w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
  line
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 2004, s. 4, for "1991" (w.e.f. 31-10-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (27991)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Delimitation of constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510&sectionId=27991&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall, in the manner herein provided, then,`
  line `distribute the seats in the House of the People allocated to each State and the seats assigned to the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of each State as readjusted on the basis of 1971 census to single-member territorial`
  line `constituencies and delimit them on the basis of the census figures as ascertained, at the ^*[census held in the`
  line `year ^1[2001]], having regard to the provisions of the Constitution, the provisions of the Act specified in`
  line `section 8 and the following provisions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) all constituencies shall, as far as practicable, be geographically compact areas, and in`
  line `delimiting them regard shall be had to physical features, existing boundaries of administrative units,`
  line `facilities of communication and public convenience;`
  line
  line `(b) every assembly constituency shall be so delimited as to fall wholly within one parliamentary`
  line constituency;
  line
  line `(c) constituencies in which seats are reserved for the Scheduled Castes shall be distributed in`
  line `different parts of the State and located, as far as practicable, in those areas where the proportion of`
  line `their population to the total is comparatively large; and`
  line
  line `(d) constituencies in which seats are reserved for the Scheduled Tribes shall, as far as practicable,`
  line `be located in areas where the proportion of their population to the total is the largest.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall--`
  line
  line `(a) publish its proposals for the delimitation of constituencies, together with the dissenting`
  line `proposals, if any, of any associate member who desires publication thereof, in the Gazette of India`
  line `and in the Official Gazettes of all the States concerned and also in such other manner as it thinks fit;`
  line
  line `(b) specify a date on or after which the proposals shall be further considered by it;`
  line
  line `(c) consider all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before the date so`
  line `specified, and for the purpose of such consideration, hold one or more public sittings at such place or`
  line `places in each State as it thinks fit; and`
  line
  line `(d) thereafter by one or more orders determine--`
  line
  line `(i) the delimitation of parliamentary constituencies; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the delimitation of assembly constituencies,`
  line
  line `of each State.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `* For the purposes of delimitation of Assembly and Parliamentary Constituencies, the words and figures "census held in the year 2001" wherever occurring, shall be construed as words and figures "census held in the year 2011" vide Act No. 34 of 2019, s. 62(1)(b) (w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
  line
  line `1 Subs. by Act 3 of 2004, s. 4, for "1991" (w.e.f. 31-10-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (27992)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Publication of orders and their date of operation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510&sectionId=27992&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall cause each of its`
  line `orders made under section 8 or section 9 to be published in the Gazette of India and in the Official`
  line `Gazettes of the States concerned and simultaneously cause such orders to be published at least in two`
  line `vernacular newspapers and publicize on radio, television and other possible media available to the public`
  line `and after such publication in the Official Gazettes of the States concerned, every District Election Officer`
  line `shall cause to be affixed, the Gazette version of such orders relating to the area under his jurisdiction, on a`
  line `conspicuous part of his office for public notice.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon publication in the Gazette of India, every such order shall have the force of law and shall`
  line `not be called in question in any court.`
  line
  line `(3) As soon as may be after such publication, every such order shall be laid before the House of the`
  line `People and the Legislative Assemblies of the States concerned.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (5), the readjustment of representation of the several`
  line `territorial constituencies in the House of the People or in the Legislative Assembly of a State and the`
  line `delimitation of those constituencies provided for in any such order shall apply in relation to every election`
  line `to the House or to the Assembly, as the case may be, held after the publication in the Gazette of India of`
  line `that order and shall so apply in supersession of the provisions relating to such representation and`
  line `delimitation contained in any other law for the time being in force or any order or notification issued`
  line `under such law in so far as such representation and delimitation are inconsistent with the provisions of`
  line `this Act:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to the delimitation orders published in relation`
  line `to the state of Jharkhand].`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall affect the representation in the House of the People or in the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of a State until the dissolution of the House or of the Assembly, as the case may be,`
  line `existing on the date of publication in the Gazette of India of the final order or orders of the Commission`
  line `relating to the delimitation of parliamentary constituencies or, as the case may be, of the assembly`
  line `constituencies of that State and any bye-election to fill any vacancy in such House or in any such`
  line `Assembly shall be held on the basis of the provisions of the laws and orders superseded by sub-section (4)`
  line `as if the said provisions had not been superseded.`
  line
  line `(6) The Commission shall endeavour to complete and publish each of its orders referred to in sub-section`
  line `(1) in the manner provided in that sub-section, ^2[within a period not later than 31st day of July,`
  line `2008] under section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2008, s. 2 (w.e.f. 14-1-2008).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "within two years of the constitution of the Commission" (w.e.f. 14-1-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (27993)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 11
  title `Deferment of delimitation in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 3, ibid.(w.e.f. 14-1-2008).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510&sectionId=27993&sectionno=10A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[(10A).Deferment of delimitation in certain cases--Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `sections 4, 8 and 9, if the President is satisfied that a situation has arisen whereby the unity and integrity of India is threatened or there is a serious threat to the peace and public order, he may, by order, defer the`
  line `delimitation exercise in a State.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_b:
  sectionId (27994)
  sectionNo 10B
  orderNo 12
  title `Delimitation Commission's order with respect to the State of Jharkhand not to have any legal effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510&sectionId=27994&sectionno=10B&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510
obj_root_law_sections_10_b_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2) of section 10, the final orders`
  line `relating to readjustment of number of seats and delimitation of constituencies in respect of the State of`
  line `Jharkhand published under the said section vide Order O.N. 63(E), dated 30th April, 2007 and O.N.`
  line `110(E), dated 17th August, 2007 shall have no legal effect and the delimitation of the constituencies as it`
  line `stood before the publication of the said Orders shall continue to be in force until the year 2026 in relation`
  line `to every election to the House of the People or to the Legislative Assembly, as the case may be, held after`
  line `the commencement of the Delimitation (Amendment) Act, 2008 (9 of 2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (27995)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to maintain delimitation orders up-to-date.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso ins. by Act 10 of 2016, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510&sectionId=27995&sectionno=11&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Election Commission may, from`
  line `time to time, by notification in the Gazette of India and in the Official Gazette of the State concerned,--`
  line
  line `(a) correct any printing mistake in any of the orders made by the Commission under section 9 or`
  line `any error arising therein from an inadvertent slip or omission; and`
  line
  line `(b) where the boundaries or name of any district or any territorial division mentioned in any of`
  line `the said orders are or is altered, make such amendments as appear to it to be necessary or expedient`
  line `for bringing the orders up-to-date, so, however, that the boundaries or areas or extent of any`
  line `constituency shall not be changed by any such notification.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the Election Commission may make such amendments, as appear to it to be`
  line `necessary or expedient, for bringing the said orders up-to-date by including therein and excluding`
  line `therefrom the relevant areas, consequent upon the exchange of one hundred and eleven enclaves of`
  line `India and fifty-one enclaves of Bangladesh with effect from 31st July, 2015, in pursuance of the`
  line `Constitution (One Hundredth Amendment) Act, 2015].`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is issued, before the`
  line `House of the People and the Legislative Assembly of the State concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (27996)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 14
  title Repeal.
  content `The Delimitation Act, 1972 (76 of 1972), is hereby repealed.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510&sectionId=27996&sectionno=12&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_200233_1517807324510
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
